What is Docker Volume? 
--> A Docker Volume is a permanent storage area where your container’s data is stored safely, even if the container is deleted.

Why Do We Need Docker Volumes?
--> To persist data, share data between containers, and safely store application data such as databases.
Containers are Ephemeral, like 
- If you delete a containers, its internal filesystem changes are lost.
- Updating images or deploying may recreate containers from scratch 
Many applications (Database,stateful services) need persistent data that survives containers deletion.

Types of Docker Volumes
--> 1. Named Volume 
A Named Volume is a volume with a user-defined name that Docker manages automatically.
--> 2. Anonymous Volumes
An Anonymous Volume is automatically created by Docker without a custom name.
--> 3. Bind Volumes
A Bind Mount connects a directory from your host machine directly into the container.
